<section id="about" class="py-16 bg-dos-bg">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="glass-card max-w-5xl mx-auto p-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl mb-12 oxanium-title text-white/90 normal-case">
                Tinkering in progress
            </h2>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 items-start">
                <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6">
                    <div class="w-full bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/10 p-8 flex flex-col gap-4 font-sans text-[10px] text-white/40 overflow-hidden">
                        <div class="flex justify-between">
                            <span>Installing curiosity...</span>
                            <span>[78%]</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="w-full h-1 bg-white/5 relative overflow-hidden">
                            <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 bg-white/40 animate-[progress_3s_ease-in-out_infinite]" style="width: 78%;"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 opacity-50">
                            <span>> trial_and_error.sh</span>
                            <span>> searching_for_why.bin</span>
                            <span class="text-dos-green">> learning_found!</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-[10px] font-pixel text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest">Iteration #4029</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="md:col-span-2 text-lg md:text-xl font-sans leading-relaxed text-white/60 space-y-8">
                    <p>
                        This garage isn't a factory; it's a playground. I am driven by <span class="text-white border-b border-white/20">pure curiosity</span> and the thrill of seeing something break in a new, interesting way. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The process is simple: <strong class="text-white font-medium italic">Try. Fail. Learn. Iterate.</strong> Let's not fear the error log; embrace it as a map to the next discovery. Every bug is just a lesson to be learnt.
                    </p>
                    <div class="pt-6 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
                        <div>
                            <span class="block text-white font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter">Try</span>
                            <span class="text-[10px] font-pixel text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest">Phase 01</span>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="block text-white font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter">Fail</span>
                            <span class="text-[10px] font-pixel text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest">Phase 02</span>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="block text-white font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter">Learn</span>
                            <span class="text-[10px] font-pixel text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest">Phase 03</span>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="block text-white font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter">Again</span>
                            <span class="text-[10px] font-pixel text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest">Phase 04</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    @keyframes progress {
        0% { width: 0%; opacity: 0.3; }
        50% { width: 78%; opacity: 1; }
        100% { width: 78%; opacity: 0.3; }
    }
</style>